article.headline: Stephen F.Austin 69, McNeese St. 56
article.story: NACOGDOCHES, Texas -- Jereal Scott scored 18 points, including 15 in the second half, to help Stephen F. Austin glide past McNeese State 69-56 on Saturday night. Scott also led the game in rebounding, pulling eight off the boards as the Lumberjacks (18-6, 8-3 Southland) took their seventh victory in their past eight outings. The Lumberjacks shot almost 60 percent from the field, faring far better than on Wednesday when they beat Northwestern State despite shooting just 37 percent. SFA got off to an early lead, keeping the Cowboys (8-16, 3-7) to just 12 points in the first half. McNeese State held its own in the second period with each team scoring 44 points, but the Cowboys couldn't overcome the early deficit. The Lumberjacks' Eddie Williams finished with 14 points and Jordan Glynn added 11. Patrick Richard led the Cowboys with 14 points.
